// Hand-authored "special" NPCs — narratively significant characters whose
// identity, faction role, position, and starting state are pinned by content.
// Background civilians do NOT live here; they're generated procedurally at
// world-init via the name pool in `data/nameGen.ts` and the appearance
// generator in `data/appearanceGen.ts`.
//
// Per-character appearance overrides live next door in `npc-appearance.json5`
// (keyed by `name`) — `setupAppearance` looks them up automatically when the
// NPC spawns.
//
// World coordinates are in pixels (TILE = worldConfig.tilePx; multiply tile
// indices by TILE in code, not here, for clarity in the spec).
//
// Adding a new special NPC: append a new entry. If they should hold a
// faction relationship, set `factionRole`. If they should look distinctive,
// add a matching entry in npc-appearance.json5. If they should occupy a
// specific workstation at world-init, set `workstation` to its specId — the
// spawn loop in ecs/spawn.ts links Workstation.occupant ↔ Job.workstation.
//
// AE complex coordinates: building origin at tile (400, 200), 28×26.
//   Board offices  — row 4, cols 9 / 13 / 17 / 21 / 25
//   Manager offices — row 10, same cols
//   Reception desk — col 3, row 13

{
  npcs: [
    // === Anaheim Electronics 董事会 (Board) ===
